         /*Answer*/: /*NO.*/ --There is no inherent stress accent in
         Jagarôth words on which the stress must always fall. That is¸
         the stress is not an inherent part of a word. Instead, the
         stress is calculated in real time according to the following
         rules:

    - (x) DETERMINE the rules for stress accent placement. 

*** /*The Rules of Stress Accent:*/ 

    - For non-compound words: 
    ~ If a word contains no long vowel or diphthong, the antepenult
      is stressed. 
    ~ If instead the ultima contains a long vowel or diphthong, the
      ultima is stressed. 
    ~ Otherwise the penult is stressed.

    - For compound words:
    ~ The first word component is ignored and the second word
      component is stress-accented as it would be were it not
      compound.

*** Examples
    - tometop :: tomato :: TOmetop :: no long vowel or diphthong present, stress on antepenult
    - kîretein ::  eagle :: kîreTEYN :: long ultima vowel causes stress on ultima
    - bûburîzeps :: in your mouth :: bûbuRÎzeps :: long vowel but not the ultima hence
      penult is stressed
    - gorgzakar :: the skull throne :: gorgZAkar :: no long vowel but only the second
      component of a compound word is stressed, hence the penult of
      /zakar/, hence gorgZAkar
    - gorgzakarôdeth :: for his skull throne :: gorgzakaRÔdeth :: long vowel but not the
      ultima hence penult is stressed 
    - jizixem :: my methamphetamine :: jiZIxem :: no long vowel hence penult is stressed
    - kîreteinôdem :: for my eagle ·  kîreteiNÔdem · long vowel but not the ultima
      hence penult is stressed
    - kîreteinashem :: from my eagle :: kîreteinAshem :: long vowel
      present but not the ultima hence the penult is stressed
    - shelelâLEPS-koi 


